quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  31,20,"Have you<sup>pl </sup>not seen that Allah has subjected to you whatever is in the heavens and whatever is in the earth and showered you with His blessings{1}, both manifest and hidden? Yet among mankind is one who argues about Allah without any knowledge nor any guidance norany illuminating Scripture.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Nafie’, Abu Amr, Hafs and Abu Ja’far read it as: “…with a blessing, both…”]
  31,21,"And when it is said to them, “Follow what Allah has sent down,” they say, “Rather, we follow what we found our forefathers doing.” Even if Satan has been calling them to the punishment of the Blaze?"
  31,22,"And whoever surrenders his face to Allah while excelling in doing good, then he has truly grasped the firmest handhold. And with Allah rests the outcome of all events."
  31,23,"And whoever denies—let not his denial sadden you<sup>sg </sup>; to Us is their{1}return, then We will inform them of what they did; indeed, Allah is All-Knowing of what lies within the chests.",footnotes:1:[A grammatical shift from singular to plural.]
  31,24,"We give them a little enjoyment, then We compel them to a harsh punishment."
  31,25,"And if you<sup>sg </sup>ask them, “Who created the heavens and the earth?” They will surely say, “Allah.” Say<sup>sg </sup>, “Praise be to Allah.” Rather, most of them do not know."
  31,26,"To Allah belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth. Indeed, Allah is the Self-Sufficient, the Praiseworthy."
  31,27,"And were all the trees on earth pens, with the sea{1}replenished{2}by seven seas following it, never would the Words of Allah run out. Indeed, Allah is Almighty, All-Wise.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Abu Amr and Ya’qub read it as: “And were all the trees on earth pens, and were the sea replenished…”],footnotes:2:[The Arabic word <i>yamuduhu</i> which means ‘replenish’ comes from the same root of the Arabic word <i>med</i><i>ā</i><i>d</i> which means ‘ink’, so it serves the meaning of ‘replenishing with ink'.]
  31,28,"Neither your<sup>pl </sup>creation nor your resurrection are but as that of a single soul. Indeed, Allah is All-Hearing, All-Seeing."
